### Version
3.0.1

### Reproduction link
[https://codepen.io/XemaA/pen/jOPEOqm?editors=0010](https://codepen.io/XemaA/pen/jOPEOqm?editors=0010)







### Steps to reproduce
I am trying to mutate  a file content's in the state so I can use them in different modules of the app.
```javascript
// In the action : I read file content
readFile(context, payload) {
    const readStream = fs.createReadStream(payload.filePath);
    Papa.parse(readStream, { header: true }, complete(results) { // here I use papaparse (Papa) to parse file content
        context.commit('testA', results.data); // in case of large file, when I comment this line the app doesn't stop
    });
}
// mutation
testA(state, payload) {
    state.structData = payload;
}
```


### What is expected?
file content mutated to state

### What is actually happening?
on case of 23MB size file the app craches without returning any errors or warning

---
When working with small files the process works as expected, the issue appears only with large files ( I am testing 23MB size file)
I am working on electron/vue app

